typeProperties.script:
source(output(
		SNo as string,
		ObservationDate as string,
		{Province/State} as string,
		{Country/Region} as string,
		{Last Update} as string,
		Confirmed as float,
		Deaths as float,
		Recovered as float
	),
	allowSchemaDrift: true,
	validateSchema: false,
	ignoreNoFilesFound: false) ~> source1
source1 select(mapColumn(
		SNo,
		ObservationDate,
		{Province/State},
		{Country/Region},
		{Last Update},
		Confirmed,
		Deaths,
		Recovered
	),
	skipDuplicateMapInputs: true,
	skipDuplicateMapOutputs: true) ~> Select1
Select1 sink(input(
		SNo as integer,
		ObservationDate as timestamp,
		ProvinceState as string,
		CountryRegion as string,
		LastUpdate as timestamp,
		Confirmed as decimal(18,2),
		Deaths as decimal(18,2),
		Recovered as decimal(18,2)
	),
	allowSchemaDrift: true,
	validateSchema: false,
	deletable:false,
	insertable:true,
	updateable:false,
	upsertable:false,
	format: 'table',
	mapColumn(
		SNo,
		ObservationDate,
		ProvinceState = {Province/State},
		CountryRegion = {Country/Region},
		LastUpdate = {Last Update},
		Confirmed,
		Deaths,
		Recovered
	),
	skipDuplicateMapInputs: true,
	skipDuplicateMapOutputs: true,
	errorHandlingOption: 'stopOnFirstError') ~> sink1

source(output(
		collectionSource as string,
		custom as (Endpoints as string[], {InUse[Yes/No]} as boolean, Name as string),
		meta as (requires as (jsonparse as string, through as string), dev as boolean),
		name as string,
		source as string,
		sourceType as string,
		type as string,
		version as string
	),
	allowSchemaDrift: true,
	validateSchema: false,
	ignoreNoFilesFound: false,
	documentForm: 'documentPerLine') ~> source1
source1 foldDown(unroll(custom.Endpoints),
	mapColumn(
		collectionSource,
		Endpoints = custom.Endpoints,
		{InUse[Yes/No]} = custom.{InUse[Yes/No]},
		CustomName = custom.Name,
		meta,
		name,
		source,
		sourceType,
		type,
		version
	),
	skipDuplicateMapInputs: false,
	skipDuplicateMapOutputs: false) ~> Flatten1
Flatten1 sink(input(
		collectionSource as string,
		custom as (Endpoints as string[], {InUse[Yes/No]} as boolean, Name as string),
		meta as (requires as (jsonparse as string, through as string), dev as boolean),
		name as string,
		source as string,
		sourceType as string,
		type as string,
		version as string
	),
	allowSchemaDrift: true,
	validateSchema: false,
	partitionFileNames:['dependmetaoutput.json'],
	partitionBy('hash', 1),
	skipDuplicateMapInputs: true,
	skipDuplicateMapOutputs: true) ~> sink1

		minAge as integer,
		maxAge as integer
	),

	validateSchema: false,
	ignoreNoFilesFound: false,
	format: 'parquet') ~> factpopulation

		StateName as string
	),
	allowSchemaDrift: true,
	validateSchema: false,
	ignoreNoFilesFound: false,
	format: 'parquet') ~> state
source(output(
		CountyName as string
	),
	allowSchemaDrift: true,
	validateSchema: false,
	ignoreNoFilesFound: false,
	format: 'parquet') ~> countyname
source(output(
		Race as string
	),
	allowSchemaDrift: true,
	validateSchema: false,
	ignoreNoFilesFound: false,
	format: 'parquet') ~> Race
source(output(
		Sex as string
	),
	allowSchemaDrift: true,
	validateSchema: false,
	ignoreNoFilesFound: false,
	format: 'parquet') ~> sex
factpopulation, state join(factpopulation@stateName == state@StateName,
	joinType:'inner',
	broadcast: 'auto')~> StateJoin
StateJoin, countyname join(factpopulation@countyName == countyname@CountyName,
	joinType:'inner',
	broadcast: 'auto')~> CountyJoin
CountyJoin, Race join(factpopulation@race == Race@Race,
	joinType:'inner',
	broadcast: 'auto')~> RaceJoin
RaceJoin, sex join(factpopulation@sex == sex@Sex,
	joinType:'inner',
	broadcast: 'auto')~> SexJoin
SexJoin sink(allowSchemaDrift: true,
	validateSchema: false,
	format: 'parquet',
	mapColumn(
		decennialTime,
		stateName = factpopulation@stateName,
		countyName = factpopulation@countyName,
		population,
		race = factpopulation@race,
		sex = factpopulation@sex,
		minAge,
		maxAge,
		stStateName = state@StateName,
		ctCountyName = countyname@CountyName,
		rRace = Race@Race,
		sSex = sex@Sex
	),
	partitionBy('hash', 1),
	skipDuplicateMapInputs: true,
	skipDuplicateMapOutputs: true) ~> OutputPop
